<dialog id="zwoModal">
  <article>
    <header>
      <h3>What is a ZWO file?</h3>
    </header>
    <p>
      A <strong>ZWO</strong> file is an XML format used to describe structured
      cycling workouts, notably on Zwift and other training platforms. It contains
      the sequence of intervals, their duration and intensity.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>You can choose one from the library.</li>
      <li>
        You can also create your own with online editors like
        <a href="https://zwofactory.com/" target="_blank">ZWO Factory</a>
        and upload them.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <footer>
      <button onclick="zwoModal.close()">Close</button>
    </footer>
  </article>
</dialog>
